---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="About | Marco Schneider"
    description="Full Stack Web Developer with experience in scalable solutions, Angular, .NET/C#, and robotics."
>
    <article class="about">
        <header class="about-header">
            <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
            <h1>Hey, I'm Marco.</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Full Stack Software Engineer</p>
        </header>

        <div class="about-body">
            <section class="about-section glass-panel">
                <h2>Background</h2>
                <p>
                    Full Stack Software Engineer with +4 years of experience delivering scalable, production-grade solutions using Angular, .NET/C#, Azure, and SQL Server in agile corporate environments. Proven track record in feature development, technical debt management, CI/CD automation, and collaborative work with Business Analysts and cross-functional teams.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Strong background in robotics, embedded systems, and applied research, including leadership in university competition teams and technical laboratory work. Adept at transforming business requirements into reliable software, mentoring peers through knowledge-transfer sessions, and maintaining high standards of code quality. Passionate about building efficient, maintainable systems and continuously improving engineering processes.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="about-section glass-panel">
                <h2>Work Experience</h2>
                
                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>ExxonMobil</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Mid-Level Full Stack Software Engineer</span>
                        <span class="experience-date">2023 – 2026</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="experience-tech">
                        Angular • .NET/C# • Azure • SQL Server • Git/GitHub • NgRx • Agile/Scrum
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Performed technical debt management activities, including issue mapping, requirement gathering, and task refinement for improvement initiatives.</li>
                        <li>Assisted Business Analysts in defining functional and technical requirements for new application features.</li>
                        <li>Led knowledge-transfer sessions on semantic versioning, GitHub Actions deployments, NgRx, and related development practices.</li>
                        <li>Facilitated Code Review sessions to maintain code quality standards, while providing and incorporating peer feedback.</li>
                        <li>Developed and maintained front-end components, particularly data visualization modules, using Google Charts integrated with NgRx for state management.</li>
                        <li>Maintained and enhanced CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions. Enhancements made reduced pipeline execution time by 20%.</li>
                        <li>Migrated database versioning workflow into the team's main API using FluentMigrator (.NET).</li>
                        <li>Maintained an application that used HangFire to schedule jobs utilizing Databricks API and Internal APIs.</li>
                        <li>Created an internal Wiki documenting business rules and architectural concepts.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>ExxonMobil</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Junior Full Stack Software Engineer</span>
                        <span class="experience-date">2022 – 2023</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="experience-tech">
                        Angular • .NET/C# • Azure • SQL Server • Git/GitHub • NgRx • Agile/Scrum
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Developed and maintained application features using Angular on the front end and .NET/C# on the backend, applying design patterns to ensure scalability and clean architecture.</li>
                        <li>Refactored and standardized front-end components, improving reusability and contributing to a more cohesive user interface.</li>
                        <li>Created unit tests and resolved bugs using diagnostic tools such as Azure App Insights to improve system reliability.</li>
                        <li>Managed code versioning with Git/GitHub and worked with Azure-hosted pipelines to support automated deployments across environments.</li>
                        <li>Gained practical experience integrating front-end, back-end, cloud services, and database layers within a corporate architecture.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>ExxonMobil</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Curitiba GBC Management Team</span>
                        <span class="experience-date">2021 – 2022</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="experience-tech">
                        Front-End Development • JavaScript • JQuery • HTML • CSS • SharePoint
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Developed and maintained internal web solutions to support event communication, workflow management, and site operations, using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and internal business processes, collaborating with cross-functional stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into functional, user-friendly interfaces.</li>
                        <li>Delivered multiple applications adopted across the Curitiba site, including: <br/>* Curitiba Site Priorities – dashboard for site-wide priorities and action tracking; <br/>* LDC Supervisor Journey – tool to support leadership on tracking information; <br/>* Curitiba Visitors Agenda – scheduling and coordination system for site visitors; <br/>* SIPAT 2022 – event website for safety week activities and communications; <br/>* Curitiba Agile Day 2022 – platform supporting event agenda and participant materials.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="about-section glass-panel">
                <h2>Other Technical Experiences</h2>

                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>Crossbots | UTFPR</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Embedded Software Developer</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="experience-tech">
                        C/C++ • Microcontroller Systems • IoT • Embedded Systems
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Developed real-time firmware for competitive autonomous line-following robots, integrating sensors, actuators, and control logic in C/C++.</li>
                        <li>Conducted iterative validation of navigation algorithms and system behavior under competition conditions: 1st place finish with robot Arthas.</li>
                        <li>Collaborated across mechanical and electronics sub-teams, ensuring hardware and firmware integration met performance requirements.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>Multiuser Photonics Laboratory | UTFPR</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Technical Research Scholar</span>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Worked with optical instrumentation for Bragg grating inscription and spectral analysis, conducting experiments and organizing safety and technical documentation.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>Electric Circuits A | UTFPR</h3>
                        <span class="experience-role">Teaching Assistant</span>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Supported laboratory classes and graded exercises.</li>
                        <li>Prepared instructional material and mentored students individually.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="about-section glass-panel">
                <h2>Education</h2>
                
                <div class="experience-item">
                    <div class="experience-header">
                        <h3>Federal University of Technology – Paraná (UTFPR)</h3>
                        <span class="experience-date">2025</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="experience-role" style="margin-bottom: 12px; display: block;">
                        Bachelors in Mechatronics Engineering
                    </div>
                    <ul class="experience-details">
                        <li>Undergraduate thesis: Performance Evaluation of Search Algorithms: A Comparison of Flood Fill, A-Star, and Dijkstra Algorithms in the Context of Micromouse Robots.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="about-section glass-panel">
                <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
                <ul class="links-list">
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://github.com/Marco-Schneider" target="_blank">GitHub</a> — open source work and side projects
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marco-antonio-schirmer-schneider-rodrigues/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> — professional history
                    </li>
                    <!-- <li><a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a> — subscribe to the blog</li> -->
                </ul>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .about {
        padding: 52px 0;
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .eyebrow {
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        color: var(--accent-main);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .about-header {
        margin-bottom: 48px;
    }
    .about-header h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .subtitle {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .about-body {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 24px;
    }
    .about-section {
        padding: 32px;
    }
    .about-section h2 {
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--accent-main);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .about-section p {
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        line-height: 1.8;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .about-section p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .about-section strong {
        color: var(--text-primary);
        font-weight: 600;
    }
    
    .experience-item {
        margin-bottom: 32px;
        padding-bottom: 32px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    }
    .experience-item:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
        padding-bottom: 0;
        border-bottom: none;
    }
    .experience-header {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        align-items: baseline;
        gap: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .experience-header h3 {
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text-primary);
        margin: 0;
    }
    .experience-role {
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--accent-main);
        font-weight: 500;
    }
    .experience-date {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-left: auto;
        font-family: monospace;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        padding: 4px 8px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .experience-tech {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        font-family: monospace;
        opacity: 0.8;
    }
    .experience-details {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 12px;
    }
    .experience-details li {
        font-size: 14.5px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        line-height: 1.6;
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 20px;
    }
    .experience-details li::before {
        content: "▹";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        color: var(--accent-main);
    }
    
    .links-list {
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 12px;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .links-list a {
        color: var(--accent-main);
        font-weight: 500;
        transition: color 0.2s, text-shadow 0.2s;
    }
    .links-list a:hover {
        color: var(--accent-secondary);
        text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--accent-glow);
    }
</style>
